subSubSection.paragraph:
Pronotum
longer than wide, tapered in front, with a pronounced fore margin depression; macrosetation long, erect, black (
Fig. 1D
). Punctures large, rather shallow, sparsely spaced, partially fused at anterior third of the pronotal surface. Intersticies among punctures smooth and shiny. Mesosternum with a distinctive posterior macrosetose area on scutum (
Fig. 1E
).
